.TH "pdcs_auto_write" 9 "pdcs_auto_write" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
pdcs_auto_write \- This function handles autoboot/search flag modifying.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "ssize_t" pdcs_auto_write
.BI "(struct kobject *kobj "  ","
.BI "struct kobj_attribute *attr "  ","
.BI "const char *buf "  ","
.BI "size_t count "  ","
.BI "int knob "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "kobj" 12
-- undescribed --
.IP "attr" 12
-- undescribed --
.IP "buf" 12
The input buffer to read from.
.IP "count" 12
The number of bytes to be read.
.IP "knob" 12
The PF_AUTOBOOT or PF_AUTOSEARCH flag
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
We will call this function to change the current autoboot flag.
We expect a precise syntax:
\"n\" (n == 0 or 1) to toggle AutoBoot Off or On
